The ruling handed down by acting Judge Clare Hartford made it possible for the National Prosecuting Authority to criminally charge abusers more than 20 years after they sexually assaulted children and adults.The challenge to the statute of limitations section was brought by the so-called Frankel 8, who accused billionaire philanthropist Sydney Frankel of abusing them decades ago when they were children.Frankel died earlier this year. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za